post_text:
Cottonwood Public School wide enrollment will be July 31st.
Enrollment will be for from 8AM to noon.
At this time you will be asked if your student will attend school on campus or would like our distance learning option. If you choose distance learning for your child, they will be responsible for all work assigned to them and graded accordingly. Our distance learning students will be enrolled with Cottonwood School and allowed to participate in school sponsored extra-curricular activities.
We are working on protocol’s to ensure safe and clean facilities/environment for our on-campus students and staff. We look forward to a great year of learning. See you July 31, 2020.

Enrollment forms are available at cottonwoodschool.net to be printed and will be available to pick up at the school soon.

Cottonwood Public School is currently seeking an energetic and highly motivated individual to join our team as a Janitor. The ideal candidate for this position is detail-oriented, flexible and willing to take on non-routine cleaning and special projects as the need arises. The Janitor will be responsible for cleaning and sanitizing offices, meeting rooms, bathrooms, public areas, etc. Please contact us on Facebook Messenger or call the office (58) 927-2937. Applications are available at cottonwoodschool.net under Administration.

Or email jdaniel@cottonwoodps.org

post_text: Cottonwood would like to thank everyone who supported our annual pie auction. Because of your support every student at Cottonwood School received a goody bag filled with apples, oranges, candy, etc., and a gift for Christmas. We love doing this for our students and couldn't do it with out all of our local business and individuals help. Thank you to Kevin Haney for being our auctioneer. And thank you Larry Cometti for getting donations for us every year. We can't name everyone who helps make this happen, but we so appreciate you all! Mr. Cody & students did a great job on the Christmas Program. Thank you Stacy for organizing and planning all the decorations, the gym looked awesome. Merry Christmas

post_text:
Cottonwood Track Parents:

We will kick off our first meet of the season this Wednesday, March 27th. We will leave the school at 7:00 am, so please have your child here at least 10 minutes before so that we can get the bus loaded. Our meet will be at Holly Creek outside of Broken Bow, so we won’t be arriving back until close to 6:00 pm. Students will be responsible for their own lunch, and we will stop by a gas station on our way to and from the meet. They shouldn’t need more than $15.

If you have any questions, feel free to call or text.

Roy Vanderburg, Head Coach
